{"questionId":"9404","questionHtml":"<p>Show that <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span> + 1 is an integrating factor for this differential equation.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em><strong>METHOD&nbsp;1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"I(t) = {{\\text{e}}^{\\int {P\\left( t \\right)} \\,{\\text{d}}t}}\">\n  <mi>I</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>e</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>∫</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>P</mi>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>(</mo>\n            <mi>t</mi>\n            <mo>)</mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n        <mrow>\n          <mtext>d</mtext>\n        </mrow>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{{\\text{e}}^{\\int {\\frac{1}{{t + 1}}} \\,{\\text{d}}t}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>e</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>∫</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mfrac>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>t</mi>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n        <mrow>\n          <mtext>d</mtext>\n        </mrow>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>= <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{{\\text{e}}^{{\\text{ln}}\\left( {t + 1} \\right)}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>e</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mtext>ln</mtext>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>(</mo>\n          <mrow>\n            <mi>t</mi>\n            <mo>+</mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>)</mo>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = t + 1\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>METHOD 2</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempting product rule differentiation on&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{\\text{d}}}{{{\\text{d}}t}}\\left( {x\\left( {t + 1} \\right)} \\right)\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>d</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>t</mi>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{\\text{d}}}{{{\\text{d}}t}}\\left( {x\\left( {t + 1} \\right)} \\right) = \\frac{{{\\text{d}}x}}{{{\\text{d}}t}}\\left( {t + 1} \\right) + x\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>d</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>t</mi>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = \\left( {t + 1} \\right)\\left( {\\frac{{{\\text{d}}x}}{{{\\text{d}}t}} + \\frac{x}{{t + 1}}} \\right)\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>d</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>d</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n          <mi>t</mi>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>t</mi>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>so <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t + 1\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span> is an integrating factor for this differential equation&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9404","referenceCode":"SPM.2.AHL.TZ0.11a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Show that t + 1 is an integrating factor for this differential equation.","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.5—Integration introduction, areas between curve and x axis","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.18—1st order DE’s – Euler method, variables separable, integrating factor, homogeneous DE using sub y=vx"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}